FlashAttention example
	FlashAttention is a python package which implements the flash-decoding idea
mentioned in https://crfm.stanford.edu/2023/10/12/flashdecoding.html. The
example seems to suggest that the optimization strategy used in the
flash-decoding idea cannot be simply implemented within the existing frameworks
of optimizers, and thus takes a rather manual hacking (700 lines) to implement
in Triton.  
